  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://data.nasa.gov/ontologies/atmonto/ATM#plannedDepartureTime">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#FunctionalProperty"/>
    <rdfs:label>planned departure time</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>The time that the flight is planned to depart per the flight plan.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="https://data.nasa.gov/ontologies/atmonto/ATM#Flight"/>
    <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://data.nasa.gov/ontologies/atmonto/NAS#SIDSTAR">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label>SIDSTAR</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>A superclass of SID and STAR defining the properties shared by both, specifically the set of common, airport, and transition routes that comprise the SID/STAR.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://data.nasa.gov/ontologies/atmonto/NAS#AirspaceInfrastructureComponent"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://data.nasa.gov/ontologies/atmonto/equipment#modeSCode">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#FunctionalProperty"/>
    <rdfs:label>mode SCode</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>The unique Mode S address of the transponder aboard the aircraft. Mode S equipment on aircraft are assigned a unique ICAO 24-bit address or (informally) Mode S hex code upon national registration and this address becomes a part of the aircraft's Certificate of Registration.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="https://data.nasa.gov/ontologies/atmonto/equipment#Aircraft"/>
    <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://data.nasa.gov/ontologies/atmonto/general#subsequenceOf">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#FunctionalProperty"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty"/>
    <rdfs:label>subsequence of</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Links a subsequence to its base sequence.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="https://data.nasa.gov/ontologies/atmonto/general#SubSequence"/>
    <rdfs:range rdf:resource="https://data.nasa.gov/ontologies/atmonto/general#Sequence"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://data.nasa.gov/ontologies/atmonto/NAS#hasTRACONid">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#FunctionalProperty"/>
    <rdfs:label>has TRACON ID</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>The FAA alphanumeric code for the TRACON.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="https://data.nasa.gov/ontologies/atmonto/NAS#TRACON"/>
    <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://data.nasa.gov/ontologies/atmonto/NAS#Sector">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label>Sector</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>A defined volume in the the airspace of an ARTCC or TRACON whose flight traffic is typically controlled by a single controller.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://data.nasa.gov/ontologies/atmonto/NAS#AirspaceInfrastructureComponent"/>
  </rdf:Description>
